## I. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

A comprehensive management system for a traditional matrimony matching portal. Leverages core C++ OOP paradigms with static memory allocation for deterministic runtime behavior, expanded further with full-stack web server capabilities via Winsock.

**CORE C++ PARADIGMS**  
▸ Class abstraction with private state and validated public interfaces  
▸ Static allocation (fixed-size vectors/arrays) for deterministic memory  
▸ Single inheritance: `UserRequest` (base) -> `PartnerMatchRequest`, `MembershipUpgradeRequest` (derived)  
▸ Method overriding for polymorphic `display()` across request types  
▸ UML modeling: Use Case, Class, State, and Sequence diagrams

**Language:** C++ (ISO C++17)  
**Memory Model:** Static allocation (Vectors/Arrays)  
**Architecture:** Full-Stack web integration & monolithic console-based interface  
**Compiler:** g++ / any C++17 compatible  

