## V. SYSTEM MODELING

Four UML diagrams model the system from different perspectives, safely mapped in the `UML/` directory.

**01 Use Case Diagram**  
Maps system functionality from the member perspective. Two actors (Member, Admin) interact with registration, filtering, and revenue use cases.

**02 Class Diagram**  
Documents static structure encompassing Profile, base UserRequests, and inherited requests, tracking encapsulation levels and dependency links.

**03 State Diagram**  
Demonstrates the distinct progressive states of user lifecycles, traveling from Unregistered -> Logged In -> Searching -> Match Accepted.

**04 Sequence Diagram**  
Traces the synchronous time-ordered message flow detailing how the Web Frontend communicates complex filtering queries to the C++ Application Logic, returning exact JSON structures.

